definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To aggregate things together into a batch.
examples: The contractor batched the purchase orders for the entire month into one statement.

definitions.definition: ( transitive , computing ) To handle a set of input data or requests as a batch process .
examples: The purchase requests for the day were stored in a queue and batched for printing the next morning.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To aggregate things together into a batch.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , computing ) To handle a set of input data or requests as a batch process .

definitions.definition: To live as a bachelor temporarily, of a married man or someone virtually married.
examples: I am batching next week when my wife visits her sister.

main_definition: ( informal ) To live as a bachelor temporarily, of a married man or someone virtually married.
